commit_message:
Use auth_token from keystonemiddleware

auth_token middleware in python-keystoneclient is deprecated and has
been moved to the keystonemiddleware repo.

Change-Id: I5f17a4ea4e81e3d10142cb92f80de8d03c94c8c6
Closes-Bug: #1342274

    curl -i -X GET $the_endpoint/trusts/ -H "X-Auth-Token: $the_token" -H ...

commit_message:
OSSN-0021 - Keystone trusts on compromised account

Adding a description of the issue of verifying Keystone trust in case
of account compromise. Including examples of API interaction to help
check the situation.

Closes-Bug: #1341849
Change-Id: Iaf38c214d553dfd4dfe29dac9dc1496c061fb765

python-keystoneclient uses this, but nothing in middleware uses it
directly.

commit_message:
remove unused dep: stevedore

This is going to be used by python-keystoneclient, but not by the
middleware directly.

Change-Id: Ia4dca0b81d36dd958f89bf0a487a84497c3ef0c6

vmwareapi: remove some unused fake vim methods

Rename_Task unused since I92acdd5cd00f739d504738413d3b63a2e17f2866

commit_message:
Revamp the symbol lookup mechanism

To complement the adjusted changes in patterns we also want
to allow the execution of patterns to be affected in a similar
manner so that symbol lookup is no longer as restrictive as it
was prior to these changes.

This change adds in the following:

- Symbol lookup by walking through an atoms contained scope/s.
- Better error messaging when symbols are not found.
- Adjusted & new tests (existing ones work).
- Better logging of the symbol lookup mechanism (helpful
  during debugging, although it is very verbose...)

Part of blueprint taskflow-improved-scoping

Change-Id: I146d4d24b7e21b6613ae33541edb5e1434635be9

commit_message:
Fix SSL with HAProxy.

The current configuration of services is that if SSL is in use (signaled by
stunnel.connect_ip) we bind to 127.0.0.1 - which is great, but it breaks
simultaneous non-SSL due to there being no pass-through stunnel equivalent on
all the nodes. As an interim measure, teach stunnel to connect to the ctlplane
address instead. We will need this flexability in future anyway to deal with
mixed-mode configurations, but we don't yet have an SSL only configuration.

The change will permit SSL only by altering the Deployment object only - the
SSL config object should now be flexible enough to run in either mode (but as
yet on an all-one-way-or-the-other basis).

Change-Id: Ibac3dec1fe7b573029482fdd9ad2d2f6223fbce0

commit_message:
Permit specification of host in stunnel templates

While we can in principle do this already, there is a bug (1344284)
in heat which breaks our ability to calculate an appropriate unified
line from within heat. Instead, we can pass separate metadata to
os-apply-config and avoid this bug (which has no straight forward
fix).

Change-Id: I820862982afee07d85f1f0ad02b08cd5b0f35e49
Related-Bug: #1344284

commit_message:
Clean up EP-Filter after delete project/endpoint

For endpoint_filter extension we should remove all the endpoint
to project associations when we delete the associated endpoint
or project. Otherwise list_endpoints_for_project and
list_projects_for_endpoint API will return 404 response if the
associated endpoint or project has been deleted. Also, there will
be a lot of dirty data remaining in the database.

Change-Id: I48e9100a8fa92d10b7ffe5f89bfb8ba9cf78a0e7
Closes-Bug: #1305537

commit_message:
Add conntrack-tools to nova dependencies

'Error deleting conntrack entries' appears in all
n-net. Adding conntrack-tools/conntrack as nova dependency,
in order to eliminate this issue.

Change-Id: Ief9deeb3349a07e22fb365e58f3368c847f845ef

@dolph: I don't think that's right here. The standard way of interacting with a session object is that you specify only the part of the URL that you actually know. For example i want to session.get('/users') and then you specify where you want to send that by endpoint_filter={'interface': 'public', 'region': 'regionOne', 'version': 3} and let the session and the auth plugin figure out the base part of the URL for you.

To expose the auth_url as a property you would have to access the auth plugin (which is just session.auth however is supposed to be transparent to users) get that url, do your own manual appending and make the full request. 

I think from an overall flow perspective rather than the call to get_endpoint() this makes more sense."}, {'account_id': 4, 'date': '2014-07-22 04:12:23.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9:

as far as i can tell, you're example of GET /users is a exactly what's wrong here- you shouldn't be using the "auth_url" to make a call to the identity service. the auth_url *should* be confined to the auth plugin, and i don't see why the session itself should have any knowledge of it.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-07-22 04:12:24.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9: -Verified

commit_message:
Add the 'auth' interface type

There are certain requests that will always want to be sent to the
auth_url.

Add a new interface type to the get_endpoint command of the base
identity plugin such that if you ask for the 'auth' interface it will
give you the auth_url.

commit_message:
Improve warning when TRIPLEO_ROOT is defaulted

The warning when TRIPLEO_ROOT was left to default to ~/.cache/tripleo
did not make it clear that other environment variables are also given
defaults based on that value. So just resetting TRIPLEO_ROOT would
not be enough to give you a working system.

This patch just makes the warning a bit clearer.

Change-Id: Idb1091c252ac83f728cb5734884c5992dd0a1754

commit_message:
Provide openstack-dn2osdbk

This tool converts docutils native XML to docbook. The conversion is
done using XSLT, with some custom XML treatment.

The XSL source is a slightly modified version of Dn2dbk written by Ãric
Bellot (http://ebellot.chez.com/dn2dbk/index.htm).

Modify doctest to check and build the HOT guide.

Implements: blueprint heat-templates

Change-Id: If866a5ffe19165c38981493684de550e0df0e36d

commit_message:
Move te-broker default IP address to 1.254

We're moving it to the end of the range to make deploys easier.
At the low end it races with dhcp agents and so forth.

Change-Id: I34600d127ff5b43c775bea07f7217cdc875b8e6a

commit_message:
Add script to prepare a ci-overcloud

Script what needs to be done in order to prepare a ci-overcloud for CI
Currently a WIP, a few things still need to be ironed out. Also run this
at the end of deploy-ci-overcloud, it currenlty hardcoded to the HP
region but so it the rest of deploy-ci-overcloud.

Co-Authored-By: Robert Collins <rbtcollins@hp.com>
Change-Id: I461a840710625294a2aef1a1e08a3ed852e946ab

commit_message:
Calculate expected number of vcpus/mem

Rather than just wait for a single vcpu or a non-zero amount of
memory to be available, we should look at the baremetal flavor and
figure out how many of each we should expect.

Closes-Bug: #1341634

Change-Id: I9d9ce55de3b9ad0f94d087179b9432e9e9e50d74

commit_message:
Wait longer for BM node registration

At present the code waits for `nova hypervisor-stats` to show the
expected number of nodes are registered. However, at this stage the
nodes can be only partially registered. This means that when the
scheduler is asked for a host, it doesn't know EG that there is ram
available and the ram filter fails.

By also waiting for memory to be registered this patch should improve
the timing characteristics and avoid this failure.

Closes-Bug: 1339532
Change-Id: I2c08bb3dee44f002442fd5c764d5dffed47ee9ba

commit_message:
Maybe install os-cloud-config from $TRIPLEO_ROOT

When running under CI we still only check the latest release of
os-cloud-config. If $ZUUL_PROJECT matches os-cloud-config, then
install it from $TRIPLEO_ROOT.

Change-Id: Ic7e86e5454d3da1b7c8de1934abce2a4bd293450

commit_message:
Update RHEL7 element since release

This patch updates the RHEL7 element to work
properly now that it has changed from beta to
release status.  It includes a repo update to
locate os-config rpms not in epel yet and an
update to the latest cloud image name.

Change-Id: I05607d62193c8f8fb1c1bece9872d456b19c5a08

libvirt: add support for memory backing parameters

Add a libvirt config class for dealing with the XML elements
under the <memoryBacking> section of the guest schema.

Blueprint: virt-driver-large-pages
Change-Id: Icd89508671a8951bed480b901b2d12d44ebb7cab

[{'created': '2014-07-21 09:17:34.000000000', 'message': 'Remove ConnectionProxy temporary class

Keystone Trusts API sends non descriptive error message for requests with
invalid trust id.
The error message only contains invalid_trust_id  instead of printing:
"Could not find trust: invalid_trust_id"
Setting kwarg "trust_id" in the exception.

Closes-Bug: #1305272

'}]
commit_message:
Adding more descriptive error message

Keystone Trusts API sends non descriptive error message for requests with
invalid trust id.
The error message only contains invalid_trust_id  instead of printing:
"Could not find trust: invalid_trust_id"
Setting kwarg "trust_id" in the exception.

Closes-Bug: #1305272
Change-Id: I35cab35ab90cf66ce7124dea142013bec9eefda9

commit_message:
debian: do not enbable grizzly repository from gplhost

There is not reason to enable this additional repository anymore.
All the important packages are either in wheezy or wheezy-backports.

Change-Id: I47af16ba6b507fc929b0d2948c757f4060ba93a5

commit_message:
Keystone LDAP domain configuration

This review extends Keystone/LDAP integration delivered with
https://review.openstack.org/106175 with a new option: instead of
reconfiguring the main identity backend, LDAP identity backend is
created as additional domain specific configuration. Main identity
backend remains SQL-based for legacy v2 support.

The keystone-ldap-domain element is delivered with
https://review.openstack.org/108117

Change-Id: Ie3ca0e81e734d256280626df76cf7699fc891688

[{'created': '2014-07-24 18:41:01.000000000', 'message': 'Idempotency for keystone initialization

This review applies some fixes needed for Keystone/LDAP integration.
Generally, when Keystone uses LDAP as backend, users are expected to be
pre-configured in LDAP. Calling user-create when keystone is connected
to LDAP will cause error, so all user-create operations must be called
only if user does not exist yet. Other initialization steps like
user/role mappings still should be called in this case, so user
existence check should not be used to determine if operation is needed.

Idempotency was already added for admin user in os-cloud-config wth
with https://review.openstack.org/100719.

Change-Id: Ifddb9f2d98307324efb7795c025cb1b0a41d7dde
'}]
commit_message:
Idempotency for keystone initialization

This review applies some fixes needed for Keystone/LDAP integration.
Generally, when Keystone uses LDAP as backend, users are expected to be
pre-configured in LDAP. Calling user-create when keystone is connected
to LDAP will cause error, so all user-create operations must be called
only if user does not exist yet. Other initialization steps like
user/role mappings still should be called in this case, so user
existence check should not be used to determine if operation is needed.

Idempotency was already added for admin user in os-cloud-config wth
with https://review.openstack.org/100719.

Change-Id: Ifddb9f2d98307324efb7795c025cb1b0a41d7dde

commit_message:
Restore instance flavor info when driver finish_migration fails

when instance resize, it will call finish_migration at last to create
new instance and destroy old instance. If driver layer has problem in
create new instance, the instance will be set to 'ERROR' state.

we are able to use reset-state --active to reset the instance and use it
but the instance information is set to new flavor
and not reverted to old one

Change-Id: I5961260f50e7893c7bf03e329e06edfd4f295640
Closes-Bug: #1296519

[{'created': '2014-07-24 18:20:41.000000000', 'message': 'Keystone/LDAP integration

The following changes were made to keystone element to provide Keystone
integration with LDAP server as authentication backend:

1. python-ldap module installed into Keystone virtual environment

2. Created a template ofr /etc/keystone/ldap.crt file which contans CA
certificates needed to connect to LDAP server, in case if TLS is
enabled. File content is expected to be passed in as
"keystone_ldap_cacertfile" field of $OVERCLOUD_EXTRA_CONFIG variable.

Configuration settings related to LDAP are supposed to be set via
passthrough feature (i.e. injected into /etc/keystone/keystone.conf file
by setting "keystone" field of $OVERCLOUD_EXTRA_CONFIG env variable).

Change-Id: I6a28e3623819b60dc411f54660c2ad714d9afb9b

commit_message:
Keystone/LDAP integration

Installs python-ldap and ldappool modules into Keystone virtual environment.

Configuration settings related to LDAP are supposed to be set via
passthrough feature (i.e. injected into /etc/keystone/keystone.conf file
by setting "keystone" field of $OVERCLOUD_EXTRA_CONFIG env variable).

Change-Id: I6a28e3623819b60dc411f54660c2ad714d9afb9b

[{'created': '2014-07-24 01:58:02.000000000', 'message': 'Revert "Cleanup apt cache after grub install"

This calls chroot as a non-root user, which will always fail with
EPERM.

This reverts commit ab2d1a31f2177b26aada075201712b0061a1b771.

Change-Id: Ie674fef694ad66e1ebc22083dec2a0bc34371e7b
'}]
commit_message:
Revert "Cleanup apt cache after grub install"

This calls chroot as a non-root user, which will always fail with
EPERM.

This reverts commit ab2d1a31f2177b26aada075201712b0061a1b771.

Change-Id: Ie674fef694ad66e1ebc22083dec2a0bc34371e7b

commit_message:
Handy utility to deep merge JSON strings

Deep-merge JSON strings provided via a command line. This can be
used to compose a JSON string for $OVERCLOUD_EXTRA_CONFIG
environment variable used for "passthrough" feature.

Change-Id: If292e490d7446f4f9ab5744526beaebfe91e20d5

commit_message:
Some clean-up to identity-admin.wadl - a few inconsistencies.

Titles for add user, update user, and delete user use wrong capitalization.
Code samples for add user and update user were incorrect.

Change-Id: I911fc04941d1a130ed40180790d3d65d18e80159

commit_message:
api: allow to retrieve resources details when listing

This allow to list resources via the generic type endpoint with adding
either ?details=true in the query or Accept: details=true in the headers.

Change-Id: I3c5dee4b0693f1234dff6137a6cb98b235a13143

commit_message:
Make OS-FEDERATION core.Driver methods abstract

Not all methods in contrib.federation.core.Driver are decorated
with @abs.abstractmethod. This patch adds missing decorators.

Change-Id: I93962110134d4b9062a75c228760333403a4f7eb

commit_message:
Add translation support to upper level modules

Added translations into modules:
 * sahara/main.py
 * sahara/context.py
 * sahara/config.py
 * sahara/exceptions.py
 * sahara/db/sqlalchemy/api.py
 * sahara/service/edp/binary_retrievers/internal_swift.py

Added change to tox.ini in section [hacking]
for pep8 passed

commit_message:
Change CirrOS type to i386 for VMWare

Because we use 32bit ESXi in our test environment, we have to use 32bit CirrOS too.

Change-Id: I272c5852cdd7b66b0f4efcc9338336ffbd6539af

commit_message:
mysql: call os-svc-enable

When configuring MySQL we should always auto-start the MySQL
daemon on startup. This prevents breaking simple use cases
like rebooting nodes, etc.

Change-Id: I15e54f54cbda2f030215f18da12f8a07ada4ca4d
Closes-bug: #1343329

commit_message:
update vsm credential correctly

Today if we modify the n1kv VSM credential in the cisco_plugins.ini, the
older VSM ip address remains in the db, and all requests are sent to
the older VSM. This patch deletes all n1kv VSM credentials on neutron
start up before adding the newer VSM credentials. Hence making sure
that there is only one n1kv VSM IP address and credential in the db.

Change-Id: I772a86bf896a1d3d9c69c545ce6918b0fe3a2e48
Closes-Bug: #1341014

The openstacklib::db::mysql resource is a library resource that can be used by nova, cinder,
ceilometer, etc., rather than replicating equivalent functionality across all
of these modules.

This resource reimplements most of the functionality of the puppetlabs
mysql::db resource. The primary purpose of writing this code from scratch
rather than using the mysql::db resource is to allow the use of a password
hash rather than a plaintext password as a parameter. Other differences from
the mysql::db implementation are:

* It does not have an ensure parameter, we will assume the db should be present
* It does not accept and execute arbitrary SQL because the db sync exec manages
  the state of the db
* It does not use ensure_resource because the database and user should only be
  created from within this resource and creating them elsewhere should be an
  error

Implements: blueprint commmon-openstack-database-resource

commit_message:
Add db::mysql and db::mysql::host_access to openstacklib

The openstacklib::db::mysql resource is a library resource that can be used by
nova, cinder, ceilometer, etc., rather than replicating equivalent
functionality across all of these modules.

This resource reimplements most of the functionality of the puppetlabs
mysql::db resource. The primary purpose of writing this code from scratch
rather than using the mysql::db resource is to allow the use of a password
hash rather than a plaintext password as a parameter. Other differences from
the mysql::db implementation are:

* It does not have an ensure parameter, we will assume the db should be present
* It does not accept and execute arbitrary SQL because the db sync exec manages
  the state of the db
* It does not use ensure_resource because the database and user should only be
  created from within this resource and creating them elsewhere should be an
  error

Implements: blueprint commmon-openstack-database-resource

Change-Id: I76bd93d1579179932d1f48cea4bb80a2576a7fba

commit_message:
Glance: make registry workers configurable

Adds glance.registry.workers parameter to control the number
of Glance Registry processes which should be started.

Change-Id: Icf299783b5e9f06f2840b2c47bff9e9bb6d9010a

commit_message:
Avoid conflicts with other tests instances

Avoid conflicts with other instances that exist, for example when
weren't deleted in other tests. Just filter out them in test that
check instances amount by server IDs

Closes-Bug: #1340382
Change-Id: I51494c9f47745810583f682caadcd8772805733a

commit_message:
VMWare: don't notify on disassociate_floatingips()

L3 agent notifications don't make sense for NSX VMWare plugin since
there is no L3 agent in such setup, so disabling them here.

Updated a unit test to check that notification is indeed not requested.

Change-Id: I9c7c32d02d466098d22df8f10448361c3d99174c
Related-Bug: 1330955

commit_message:
Tries to get NIC by name if mac was changed

Fuel loses nodes when some node was added to cluster and then mac-addresses
of NICs have been changed. Since now the issue is fixed.

The fix is based on the assumption that a NIC name is unique within a
node, and if we can't get an interface by MAC, we can try to get it by
name.

Closes-Bug: #1282568
Change-Id: I612a183d51ebb00afbf753ae3ee8dbccac54a4c4

commit_message:
Raise DBReferenceError on foreign key violation

SQLAlchemy session code now parses foreign key violations and returns a
new custom exception so we can track them.

Change-Id: If5610b5743203a5c34ac7df240e5332c39911c4a

[{'created': '2014-07-25 10:37:25.000000000', 'message': "Sync RPC module from oslo

This change syncs the following patches from oslo-incubator RPC:
- I67923cb024bbd143edc8edccf35b9b400df31eb3
- Ia148baa6e1ec632789ac3621c85173c2c16f3918

RabbitMQ: advance thru the list of brokers on reconnect

In RabbitMQ implementation, when using multiple rabbit_hosts, we don't want to
immediately retry failed connection for the same failed broker. This was not
the case in existing implementation though, where we've always attempted to
reconnect starting from the first broker in the list of candidates. So if the
first broker failed, we initiated reconnect to the same failed broker.

This change makes reconnect() implementation to select the next broker in the
list. This also means that non-failure reconnect attempts will also switch the
current broker. All in all, users should not rely on any particular order to
use brokers from the list, so this should not constitute an issue.

Qpid: advance thru the list of brokers on reconnect

In Qpid implementation, when using multiple qpid_hosts, we don't want to
immediately retry failed connection for the same failed broker. This was not
the case in existing implementation though, where we've always attempted to
reconnect starting from the first broker in the list of candidates. So if the
first broker failed, we initiated reconnect to the same failed broker.

This change makes reconnect() implementation to select the next broker in the
list. This also means that non-failure reconnect attempts will also switch the
current broker. All in all, users should not rely on any particular order to
use brokers from the list, so this should not constitute an issue.

Partial-Bug: #1261631
Change-Id: Ie9c4de2c094a5d420acca5e4a49ee6a36279ed87

commit_message:
Sync RPC module from oslo, fixing reconnect failures

This change syncs the following patches from oslo-incubator RPC:
- I67923cb024bbd143edc8edccf35b9b400df31eb3
- Ia148baa6e1ec632789ac3621c85173c2c16f3918

RabbitMQ: advance thru the list of brokers on reconnect

In RabbitMQ implementation, when using multiple rabbit_hosts, we don't want to
immediately retry failed connection for the same failed broker. This was not
the case in existing implementation though, where we've always attempted to
reconnect starting from the first broker in the list of candidates. So if the
first broker failed, we initiated reconnect to the same failed broker.

This change makes reconnect() implementation to select the next broker in the
list. This also means that non-failure reconnect attempts will also switch the
current broker. All in all, users should not rely on any particular order to
use brokers from the list, so this should not constitute an issue.

Qpid: advance thru the list of brokers on reconnect

In Qpid implementation, when using multiple qpid_hosts, we don't want to
immediately retry failed connection for the same failed broker. This was not
the case in existing implementation though, where we've always attempted to
reconnect starting from the first broker in the list of candidates. So if the
first broker failed, we initiated reconnect to the same failed broker.

This change makes reconnect() implementation to select the next broker in the
list. This also means that non-failure reconnect attempts will also switch the
current broker. All in all, users should not rely on any particular order to
use brokers from the list, so this should not constitute an issue.

Partial-Bug: #1261631
Change-Id: Ie9c4de2c094a5d420acca5e4a49ee6a36279ed87

commit_message:
Calculate a suitable column width for positional arguments

Overwrite the method add_arguments in the class
OpenStackHelpFormatter to calculate a suitable columnt width
(max_help_position) for the positional arguments.

example output before this patch:

    ec2-credentials-create
                        Create EC2-compatible credentials for user per tenant.
    ec2-credentials-delete
                        Delete EC2-compatible credentials.
    ec2-credentials-get
                        Display EC2-compatible credentials.
    ec2-credentials-list
                        List EC2-compatible credentials for a user.

example output after this patch:

    ec2-credentials-create  Create EC2-compatible credentials for user per
                            tenant.
    ec2-credentials-delete  Delete EC2-compatible credentials.
    ec2-credentials-get     Display EC2-compatible credentials.
    ec2-credentials-list    List EC2-compatible credentials for a user.

Change-Id: Ibd5d3502022d2afcfd4f57fef9a0bbf23d34b767
Closes-Bug: #1326471

commit_message:
Prevent error message when creating a user

keystone changed behaviour and didn't add the user
to the specified role. Now it does; this patch
prevents an exception popping up without breaking
with previous versions.

Change-Id: I115a5126b70ae3c7733aa065bf55104f88cc42e5
Closes-Bug: #1260439
(cherry picked from commit f5ded29d9a73db4c225cbfb664e7d85e5aa0996b)

commit_message:
fix pexpect.spawn.closed typo - no such method

the pexpect.spawn.closed method does not exist, but pexpect.spawn.close
does. The test code used the former which caused unpredictable method
missing errors.

Change-Id: I32da783aa1e274a45f0b685522b829d67dae7970

commit_message:
Fixed bug with empty "volumes" when heat engine is used

Now if user creates cluster using heat engine, field "volumes"
contains list of volume IDs.

Change-Id: Ie53f3b2f4ce2ac4a6fb7f67422a2fb0eb474c5b5
Closes-bug: #1278908

commit_message:
Add template version for the provider template

The unittest "test_properties_type_mismatch" in
test_provider_template.py, the provider template misses the template
version, so there will be a "missing template version" exception, not
the expected "type mismatch" exception.

Closes-Bug: #1325146
Change-Id: Id836a7bd31dcbb4072743560cc1b314fc3073852

commit_message:
Deadlocks and random CI tests failures are fixed

Code partially refactored to proper use of DB transactions:
 - receiver partially refactored from DB models to Nailgun objects
 - locking of objects added into reveiver
 - task manager partially refactored
 - DB commits removed from receiver
 - weird DB commit removed from Nailgun task object
 - weird logic for repeating tests on deadlocks removed
 - in fake tasks reveiver methods calling wrapped by try/except
 - filtering of empty collection in NailgunCollection fixed
 - ordering by id added into getting Task object by uuid in case of locking
 - values from consts module used instead hardcoded values in many places

Implements blueprint nailgun-db-transactions
Closes-Bug: #1340703

Change-Id: I520efc9a4b0b52feae4b86309da653ade50c7c9c

commit_message:
Upgrades, fix rollback for bootstrap engine

* changed rollback strategy for bootstrap
  upgrade engine, in previous strategy we
  made symlink from previous version of
  bootstrap to /var/www/nailgun/bootstrap
  it doesn't work because in 5.0 version
  cobbler container mounts /var/www/nailgun
  directory as /repo, as result symlinks
  which we make on the host system are
  broken inside of container.

  Instead of symlink command we rename
  previous version to /var/www/nailgun/bootstrap

* use lexists instead of exists because
  exists returns False on broken symlinks

* fixed docker engine rollback, there
  was wrong definition of previous version
  of fuel

Change-Id: Id0b50835410e005fde76f421981b4616211ddcbf
Closes-bug: #1348166

  exists returns False on broken symlinks

* fixed docker engine rollback, there

commit_message:
Additional SELinux scripts

Created wrapper scripts around semanage fcontext and
restorecon commands.

For a lay person, these scripts are easier to understand. We also
check if SELinux is available within the script, so it will reduce
the amount of code currently in the SELinux orc scripts when they
are refactored.

Change-Id: I7fdd7d52e255a50d4900f35aba4b3390c68e6651

Tune down the node_locked_retry_interval and
node_locked_retry_attempts config options for tests. The commit
428c24767575419d5b472b52f2b622588a3a7253 introduced a new retry mechanism
for the NodeLocked exception but the config options weren't resetted for
the tests so the tests verifying that exception were wasting time sleeping.

Closes-Bug: #1348586
Change-Id: Ia516ede357b00ebb19d10f2f603a3e766478c1b3
"}]
commit_message:
Tune down node_locked_retry_{attempts,interval} config for tests

Tune down the node_locked_retry_interval and
node_locked_retry_attempts config options for tests. The commit
428c24767575419d5b472b52f2b622588a3a7253 introduced a new retry mechanism
for the NodeLocked exception but the config options weren't resetted for
the tests so the tests verifying that exception were wasting time sleeping.

Closes-Bug: #1348586
Change-Id: Ia516ede357b00ebb19d10f2f603a3e766478c1b3

[{'created': '2014-07-25 09:33:22.000000000', 'message': 'Add RPC version to test_get_driver_properties

We should be explicit about which version is required by that RPC
call. The test works now because it needs the current last RPC version
(1.16), but any subsequent update on the RPC layer will cause that test
to fail.

Change-Id: I77d8ad8486a1ae58ed150bb08acc99b0f55792c3
'}]
commit_message:
Add RPC version to test_get_driver_properties

We should be explicit about which version is required by that RPC
call. The test works now because it needs the current last RPC version
(1.16), but any subsequent update on the RPC layer will cause that test
to fail.

Change-Id: I77d8ad8486a1ae58ed150bb08acc99b0f55792c3

Ihar, thanks for your comment. If I understand it correctly the spec you proposed is to address the eventlet-mysql deadlock problem using a client that works better with eventlet. Even if you solve that issue there's the possibility of getting a deadlock when performing a transaction on a relational database. The possibility is even higher in case of HA setups. The recommendation in that case is to retry the transaction, see http://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/5.0/en/innodb-deadlocks.html. That is what I am trying to do here. Or maybe you are implying that the client you are proposing will retry the transaction ? (3 comments)

Thanks for posting this change. I have seen some deployments where this functionality is needed when the scale increases.

Unfortunately I think that in its current form it is a little too risky to merge.

Most importantly, there should be some sort of limit on how long to retry when a deadlock is encountered.

Once you do implement a limit, some other issues arise. You then have two parameters which may need to be tweaked depending on the deployment, and should therefore be configurable:

 a) Retry limit
 b) Interval between retries

Now the easiest way to provide this is with config options.

(But wouldn't it be nice for admins of they could tweak these parameters "on the fly" to see what works best, or adjust them as the characteristics of the deployment change? This would mean providing an admin API for them. I am not saying this should be done now. Just airing my crazy thoughts.)'}, {'account_id': 9656, 'date': '2014-07-17 08:50:35.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 6: Code-Review-1

commit_message:
Add retry_on_deadlock decorator to retry DB operations

Port retry_on_deadlock decorator from nova
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/22276 . Add this decorator to some
methods in db_base_plugin and ml2 plugin, to retry a transaction if it
gets rolled back because of a deadlock. Deadlocks are a classis problem
in relational DB and they are due to the fact that no operation is really
atomic.

Fixes-bug: 1338606
Change-Id: Ie155cb2efa67b34f7c1435c243d3f3658bfcd7e3

commit_message:
Sync apiclient from oslo-incubator

Need to sync the latest apiclient from oslo-incubator to make nova
cli cache work. Command used:
python update.py --base novaclient --dest-dir ../python-novaclient/ \
--modules apiclient

syncd patches:

commit_message:
Fix booting from volume when using api v3

The current code in novaclient/base.py, class BootingManagerWithFind
do not take in account the differences required to boot an instance from
a volume in API v3. V3 expects UUID as volume id and also the source type
to be set.

Change-Id: Id8cfb2d7811aead27cb26cf7ff615c7a9ed05d54

commit_message:
Description is mandatory parameter when creating Security Group

As per the bug, description should not be a mandatory parameter
as it creates inconsistency with other opestack items which has
description as an optional parameter.

So in the fix, the description argument has been made optional.
The old command was:
nova secgroup-create <name> <description>
Now new command will be:
nova secgroup-create <name> [<description>]

Patch updated based on the comments received

Updated commit message for gerrit autolink

Closes-Bug: #1332133
Change-Id: I2ded915be4a57f3c46e6cf5d1bf00e8c917cd0b9

commit_message:
Add "version-list" for listing REST API versions

Nova provides REST API versions.
This patch adds a subcommand "version-list" for outputting the versions.

Change-Id: I1b40ad57912aa740c0b1d9221018aba9b13a5436

commit_message:
Replace UserManager with None in tests

Don't access keystoneclient's UserManager in tests. This should be
considered private data of keystoneclient and is not actually used by
horizon tests.

Conflicts:
	openstack_dashboard/test/test_data/keystone_data.py

Change-Id: I261e79b31dfc7388adb3dc63a3a5e54042f05e54
Closes-Bug: #1347236
(cherry picked from commit 821619fff324ba1bc3f697f585a0c350573f24a2)

commit_message:
sync periodic_task fix from incubator

Set the value of time the periodic task was last run to a multiple of the
spacing value rather than the actual last time run. This ensures tasks runs
regularly but avoids synchronizing that interval with other nodes.

This patch also removes the coalescing of tasks which are _nearby_ (0.2
seconds away).

4dbd3aa Make periodic tasks run on regular spacing interval
21249f1 Fix parenthesis typo misunderstanding in periodic_task

Change-Id: I8873545578f104fd204fbc25493350128b2bc8d4

commit_message:
Fix exception names and CLI args

Fixes two bugs:
* Renames HTTPNotFound -> NotFound to match openstack.common.exceptions
* Fixes positional argument names (package-id -> id with metavar) and
  adds shell tests to check parsing
* Uses temporary files in unit tests to correct intermittent test failure

Change-Id: I273e9af6e55f20965b143290c207e88ee062b0c0
Closes-Bug: #1339208

commit_message:
Add taskflow library as a distinct project

The taskflow-core team includes members who are not all in oslo-core, so
it is useful to be able to track their stats separately.

Change-Id: I6508460c0d2a00f76d6f7c8bcf348b1e098a907f

commit_message:
cinder-volume: install qemu-img for conversions

Updates the cinder-volume element so that it installs the
qemu-img package. This is required in order to support
boot from volume conversions from Glance images (qcow2).

Change-Id: I1c6fb4692166b173092395967ffe9fe88ffdb602
Partial-bug: #1340479

Updates the cinder element to provide a new top level configuration
for cinder.image_conversion_dir. We are doing this as a top level

commit_message:
Create/configure cinder's image_conversion_dir

Updates the cinder element to provide a new top level configuration
for cinder.image_conversion_dir. We are doing this as a top level
config because we also want to create this directory on disk as
well... and using os-apply-config to supply that default makes
sense. (using the pass-thru config would seem to be a bad choice
for this given we need to create a directory if it is set).

The cinder-volume element has been updated to create the
configured image_conversion_dir. If no image_conversion_dir
the default value is created at /mnt/state/var/lib/cinder/conversion.

Change-Id: Ibe8c20b7c815bb84d40a8593e51e82be95e01ec0
Closes-bug: #1340479

commit_message:
Adding start/end time to data processing-job execution details

For the data processing -> job execution -> details page, we
are adding start/end time for the job execution as details
for the job execution being viewed.

Change-Id: I931c836630f4a7a58f7c0b60161cfca6bbba9ee1
Closes-Bug: bug #1336028
Co-Authored-By: Andrew Lazarev <alazarev@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
Add a local datasource collector to occ

This spec details adding a local datasource collector to
os-collect-config. The collector will collect configuration data from
well known directories, allowing multiple elements to install and apply
configuration data to an instance in the same image build. This will allow
elements to supply configuration data for runtime consumption.

Change-Id: I221a38dff2064ff0df0628140d80498949c6d16d

commit_message:
Use /usr/bin/env python instead of /usr/bin/python

The usage of /usr/bin/env ensures that the first interpreter
found in the environment's $PATH variable is used. This should
be preferred.

Change-Id: Icb9be2b208ae95f30d25f5645f9ba864efabcdd7

commit_message:
Adding sanitization for trusts in JobExecution model

Although there is no data model update to JobExecution there are some
minor changes to ensure that trust ids don't leak from the JobExecution
representations.

Changes
* adding sanitizing for trusts to the JobExecution Resource
* adding testing for trusts filter from JobExecution

Partially implement: blueprint edp-swift-trust-authentication
Change-Id: If88bba39efdab01195878a5b1d43bb6c975531b9

commit_message:
Rename os-config-applier to os-apply-config

Since 1fde418207c004744dcc0d510bd88973ec05721a, os-config-applier is
deprecated. os-apply-config should be used instead.

Without this change, OS::Heat::SoftwareDeployment is broken because
the heat-config file is not created anymore in
/usr/libexec/os-apply-config/templates/var/run/heat-config.

Change-Id: I75d423f9fe15f2edaadba71174c4c20a3b2cd873

commit_message:
Create snapshots if preparing of slaves fails

When some slave nodes do not bootstrap properly
while preparing slaves for further deployments
system test fails. In such cases tests should create
VMs snapshots to be able investigate why nodes
didn't boot over network.

Change-Id: Id6926637fe940dc29c0e5eb3e59a06f96e310363
Closes-bug: #1348249

Add fuel_version to cluster_tags

Adding fuel_version tag to cluster_tags
we guarantee that tests will be rediscovered
after cluster is updated

commit_message:
Use SQLAlchemy cursor execute events for tracing

This change provides a consistent
system of intercepting statement executions, gaining information
about the current stack trace, and then injecting that information
either into the statement and/or logging it.   The system
works for any backend without the need to code to DBAPI
details or monkeypatching of the cursor.

Change-Id: If80db9a0a898d2cb94837ff059fc054590050506

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-07-11 20:56:57.000000000', 'message': 'Port _is_db_connection_error check to exception filters

The last part where we are handling DB exceptions is the
_is_db_connection_error() function, which is called within a retry
loop inside of session.create_engine() to perform an initial
connection test.  SQLAlchemy currently does not run "connect"
errors through the exception handling system.  In order to have
these exceptions participate in the filtering system, add
a new function handle_connect_error(engine) which runs
engine.connect() and feeds the exception into the
handler(context) system directly, producing a compatible context
that the filters can use.   Refactor the looping mechanism within
session.create_engine() into a separate function _test_connection()
so that the logic is encapsulated and can be tested.

Change-Id: Iad1bac9d0f9202b21e4c9c170aa84494b770728d

commit_message:
Port _is_db_connection_error check to exception filters

The last part where we are handling DB exceptions is the
_is_db_connection_error() function, which is called within a retry
loop inside of session.create_engine() to perform an initial
connection test.  SQLAlchemy currently does not run "connect"
errors through the exception handling system.  In order to have
these exceptions participate in the filtering system, add
a new function handle_connect_error(engine) which runs
engine.connect() and feeds the exception into the
handler(context) system directly, producing a compatible context
that the filters can use.   Refactor the looping mechanism within
session.create_engine() into a separate function _test_connection()
so that the logic is encapsulated and can be tested.

partially implement bp: use-events-for-error-wrapping

Change-Id: Iad1bac9d0f9202b21e4c9c170aa84494b770728d

[{'created': '2014-07-11 20:56:57.000000000', 'message': 'Integrate the ping listener into the filter system.

Replace the use of the connection pool "checkout" event
for "pinging" a connection with the use of the Connection.begin()
event.  This event corresponds to the start of a transaction, so
will "ping" the connection for every transaction rather than just
on checkout, and by running at the level of Connection rather
than the pool, we have access to the whole range of services we
need, including that we can emit a core "select([1])" that will
work on all backends, we get the use of the handle_error() event,
and we get the built in checking for "is disconnect" as well
as the engine/pool being invalidated or disposed as is appropriate
for the SQLAlchemy version in use.  The begin() event is a safe
place to recycle the connection from an invalid state back to
a ready state.

Change-Id: Ic29e12f1288f084a5e727101686dd71b12a5787b

commit_message:
Integrate the ping listener into the filter system.

Replace the use of the connection pool "checkout" event
for "pinging" a connection with the use of the Connection.begin()
event.  This event corresponds to the start of a transaction, so
will "ping" the connection for every transaction rather than just
on checkout, and by running at the level of Connection rather
than the pool, we have access to the whole range of services we
need, including that we can emit a core "select([1])" that will
work on all backends, we get the use of the handle_error() event,
and we get the built in checking for "is disconnect" as well
as the engine/pool being invalidated or disposed as is appropriate
for the SQLAlchemy version in use.  The begin() event is a safe
place to recycle the connection from an invalid state back to
a ready state.

partially implement bp: use-events-for-error-wrapping

Change-Id: Ic29e12f1288f084a5e727101686dd71b12a5787b

[{'created': '2014-07-11 16:44:19.000000000', 'message': 'Add disconnect modification support to exception handling

This patch backports an additional feature from the
SQLAlchemy 0.9.7 handle_error() event, the ability to alter the
"is disconnect" status of an exception.  In this case, the
supported case is only to take an exception that's not a disconnect,
and to graduate it to a disconnect.  Going in the other direction
isn't possible with the approach here because the connection invalidation
would already have taken place, as we are wrapping the _handle_dbapi_error()
method.

We may want to be able to promote an exception to "is disconnect" in
cases where special database configurations or backends such as that of
Percona have complex detection scenarios not covered by SQLAlchemy's
provided backends.

partially implement bp: use-events-for-error-wrapping

Change-Id: I23a4da2dc39af015a01d6d587c57c5e1c4b95f31

commit_message:
Add disconnect modification support to exception handling

This patch backports an additional feature from the
SQLAlchemy 0.9.7 handle_error() event, the ability to alter the
"is disconnect" status of an exception.  In this case, the
supported case is only to take an exception that's not a disconnect,
and to graduate it to a disconnect.  Going in the other direction
isn't possible with the approach here because the connection invalidation
would already have taken place, as we are wrapping the _handle_dbapi_error()
method.

We may want to be able to promote an exception to "is disconnect" in
cases where special database configurations or backends such as that of
Percona have complex detection scenarios not covered by SQLAlchemy's
provided backends.

partially implement bp: use-events-for-error-wrapping

Change-Id: I23a4da2dc39af015a01d6d587c57c5e1c4b95f31

commit_message:
add internal delete notification for endpoint

I think endpoint is not an important resource which other projects would
pay close attention to. So I think an internal notification is enough.

Change-Id: Ie42f2c867ea70fd41583151da0be19b9db682dad
Closes-Bug: #1337763

commit_message:
Change UI descriptions of Mellanox components

This commit include changes for Mellanox UI:
  1. Change UI descriptions to better explain restrictions.
  2. Move number of virtual NICs beneath Mellanox SR-IOV
     plugin.
  3. Add opposite restrictions to openstack.yaml.

Closes-bug: #1346224

Change-Id: I2d7d218ac465e7be9e3b9650dc972051bde1b165
Signed-off-by: Aviram Bar-Haim <aviramb@mellanox.com>

commit_message:
Minor cleanup of utils unit test

This patch removes an unnecessary stream seek from one test,
and renames a couple other tests to reflect the refactoring
of the filter_stream function into two separate functions.

Rename virtutils to the more common libvirt_utils

`libvirt_utils` is the more prevalent alias in the code for the module, so
rename `virtutils` to match.

Change-Id: Ib8d4291866bc53fa1980b70dd0f12e6b1fe10436

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly
    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. The more you
    participate in the community the more rewarding it is for you. You may also
    notice that the more you get to know people and get to be known, the faster
    your patches will be reviewed and eventually approved. Get to know others
    and become known by doing code reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a
    great way to learn the code base.

    Thanks again for supporting OpenStack, we look forward to working with you.

    IRC: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/IRC
    Workflow: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Gerrit_Workflow

'}, {'created': '2014-06-28 21:17:33.000000000', 'message': 'Modify L3 Agent for Distributed Routers

This patch is an enhancement to the existing L3
Agent. This allows the L3 Agent to run in
Distributed mode.  This patch is a part of
Neutron OVS Distributed Router Blueprint
neutron-ovs-dvr.

Supports distributed routers by enhancing the router
object to function across multiple nodes.

Utilized two new types of namespaces:
-FIP to handle multiple VM fips and routers per node
-SNAT to handle centralized SNAT per router

New configuration params are used to notify l3-scheduler
what each agent supports.

Rules and tables are enhanced and added to support
routing across distributed routers without going to
a centralized router.

Co-Authored-By: Rajeev Grover <rajeev.grover@hp.com>
DocImpact: new config params, functional, and deployment changes
Partially-Implements: blueprint neutron-ovs-dvr
Change-Id: Icead821bb74372b15aac2e5cefe8ad7f08c037ab

'}, {'created': '2014-07-07 16:42:53.000000000', 'message': "Modify L3 Agent for Distributed Routers

This patch is an enhancement to the existing L3 Agent.
This allows the L3 Agent to support distributed routers
by enhancing the router object to function across
multiple nodes.

Utilized two new types of namespaces:

- FIP to handle multiple VM fips and routers per node
- SNAT to handle centralized SNAT per router

Rules and tables are enhanced and added to support routing
across distributed routers without going to a centralized
router.

Finally, a new configuration param 'agent_mode' is introduced
and it controls what the L3 agent can do: the available values
are: 'legacy', 'dvr', 'dvr_snat' (more details inline).

The l3-scheduler uses the newly introduced agent_mode to
determine what L3 agent to select during the scheduling
process.

Partially-Implements: blueprint neutron-ovs-dvr

DocImpact

Change-Id: Icead821bb74372b15aac2e5cefe8ad7f08c037ab
Co-Authored-By: Rajeev Grover <rajeev.grover@hp.com>

Rules and tables are enhanced and added to support routing
across distributed routers without going to a centralized
router.

Finally, a new configuration param 'agent_mode' is introduced
and it controls what the L3 agent can do: the available values
are: 'legacy', 'dvr', 'dvr_snat' (more details inline).

The l3-scheduler uses the newly introduced agent_mode to
determine what L3 agent to select during the scheduling
process.

Partially-Implements: blueprint neutron-ovs-dvr

DocImpact

Change-Id: Icead821bb74372b15aac2e5cefe8ad7f08c037ab
Co-Authored-By: Rajeev Grover <rajeev.grover@hp.com>

commit_message:
Modify L3 Agent for Distributed Routers

This patch is an enhancement to the existing L3 Agent.
This allows the L3 Agent to support distributed routers
by enhancing the router object to function across
multiple nodes.

Utilized two new types of namespaces:

- FIP to handle multiple VM fips and routers per node
- SNAT to handle centralized SNAT per router

Rules and tables are enhanced and added to support routing
across distributed routers without going to a centralized
router.

Finally, a new configuration param 'agent_mode' is introduced
and it controls what the L3 agent can do: the available values
are: 'legacy', 'dvr', 'dvr_snat' (more details inline).

The l3-scheduler uses the newly introduced agent_mode to
determine what L3 agent to select during the scheduling
process.

Partially-Implements: blueprint neutron-ovs-dvr

DocImpact

Change-Id: Icead821bb74372b15aac2e5cefe8ad7f08c037ab
Co-Authored-By: Rajeev Grover <rajeev.grover@hp.com>

commit_message:
Added vcenter support for ostf tests.

Because in the configuration with vCenter compute node is missing, added:
1. Getting type of virtualization from cluster settings
2. Processing case when the type of virtualization is vmvare (not checked for no compute node available)
3. In test_sanity_infrastructure compute node has been replaced by a controller because
   for vmvare and neutron interaction occurs via controller node

Implements: blueprint vcenter-hv-full-scale-support
Change-Id: I4f74011de5548990f163f220632fbf4fe2ffa39e

commit_message:
firewall-rule-show is not showing protocol "any"

If user creates a firewall rule with protocol = any, firewall-rule-show of
that rule is not showing anything. It should display "any".

Change-Id: I726bd4990fcefac1927acc503913434b52e1f413
Closes-bug: 1336800

commit_message:
Do not log unconfigured collector as warning

The configuration will dictate whether or not something is configured.
If it is not, this is a normal state and should not be logged as a
warning.

Change-Id: I479f0aed5837871009bc69fa028f5eb64a060c53
Closes-Bug: #1321551

commit_message:
Unit Testing TripleO Projects

The TripleO projects as a whole are light on unit test coverage,
which makes reviews and refactoring more difficult and means that
less-used code paths often just don't work.  This spec proposes
some steps that can be taken to improve the unit testing situation.

Change-Id: I6a9c3e5b4a34b0b1ba88598d1597e6940c11bcc1
Partial-Blueprint: unit-testing

commit_message:
Ensure routing key is specified in the address for a direct producer

This change is already merged in oslo-incubator.  Original commit
message body includes:

    Porting this fix from oslo.messaging.  This fixes the impl_qpid.py
    driver to allow it to work with the latest stable upstream QPID broker
    (version 0.28).  See the Apache Qpid Jira bug
    https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPID-5557

Change-Id: If71f78e50f8a9b3acfd1e9d02c8271f17c4ebee7
Related-Bug: #1300318
(cherry picked from commit 3597ffca77133101943114b80fd4263bada87f4f)

commit_message:
Fix FloatingIP.save() when updating fixed_ip attr

When fixed_ip attribute of FloatingIP instance is changed,
db.floating_ip_update() call will fail with an SQLAlchemy traceback.
This happens because we are trying to pass SA a FixedIP object rather
than FixedIp model instance it actually expects. In addition to this,
FloatingIP.save() expects db.floating_ip_update() to return an
updated instance, while it (mistakenly) always returns None.

This effectively fixes live migration of VMs between compute nodes
when the former have floating IPs assigned.

Closes-Bug: #1334164

Change-Id: I69366360cabfe119f08eaae14eb2171d5b3c5c98

[{'created': '2014-05-06 12:24:47.000000000', 'message': 'Control mechanism for os-apply-config

At present, there is no way for os-apply-config (oac) to determine:
 * Whether to create an empty file if there is no content
 * What the permissions should be set to on the target file

Beyond this, there are also requests under consideration for:
 * Multiple templating stages
 * Production of multiple files from a single template

Solving the problem as described requires a mechanism to control oac
output besides the file content. The basic proposal is to parameterise
oac with a map (aka dictionary) containing control data. This map will
be supplied via a YAML mapping within a clearly demarcated header.

Change-Id: I8fe7126d7261c1f106d7413bd31aa379e9ae5c3e

commit_message:
Control mechanism for os-apply-config

We require a control mechanism in os-apply-config (oac). This could be
used, for example, to:
  * Not create an empty target
  * Set permissions on the target

Change-Id: I8fe7126d7261c1f106d7413bd31aa379e9ae5c3e

commit_message:
Clean up EP-Filter after delete project/endpoint

For endpoint_filter extension we should remove all the endpoint
to project associations when we delete the associated endpoint
or project. Otherwise list_endpoints_for_project and
list_projects_for_endpoint API will return 404 response if the
associated endpoint or project has been deleted. Also, there will
be a lot of dirty data remains in the database.

Change-Id: Ib65fe5233313ff23a288b1b688705ae098afa547
Closes-Bug: #1305537

commit_message:
OFAgent: Share codes of l2-population in OVS agent

This is step 1 implementation of OFAgent l2-population.
OFAgent partially uses codes in OVS agent on implementation of l2-population.
We share these codes adding mixin class for OVS to l2-population rpc.
We use a ryu library instead of executing a ovs-vsctl command
and on OFAgent l2-population is no longer optional.
Also a function of local arp responder will be implemented on step 2.

related commit: b6133c35dd587f6b01e8ec12757347b2767713a6

Partially implements: blueprint ofagent-l2pop

Change-Id: I99a2adfd380a9fefe34c53e0dabc21d8cf5936cc

commit_message:
Setup for translation

To start translation, we need to initially import the
translation file - and place it at the proper place so that
the usual CI scripts can handle it.

The proper place is for all python projects
$PROJECT/locale/$PROJECT.pot - see setup.cfg.

Further imports of po files will be done by the OpenStack Proposal
bot once manila has moved to openstack and setup the usual
translation jobs as part of gating. This change ensures that the gating
jobs will do the right thing.

Change-Id: I71ca9e8c0e4ea5586c1f1616607dddec595f65b6

commit_message:
Remove warn log for over quota

Over quota exception is already raised at API layer
and no need to print a warning log.

Change-Id: If44d5f2dd0e11d15d57cf6ab247f5e9e7fe75a9c

commit_message:
Move hbase alarms driver code to alarm tree

This change move the alarms related code of hbase driver to
the alarm storage subtree.

Partial implements blueprint dedicated-alarm-database

Change-Id: I03f4f4e0399b460e5a5caaa49f95f805fb026a64

commit_message:
Use oslo.db in manila

Use oslo.db library instead of own implementation.

Oslo.db code contains different utils for work with db api, db session,
migrations, test classes for db testing, tools for automatic retry
db.api query if db connection was lost, etc.

Oslo.db code was tested better as it is currently used in many projects,
there will be no need in testing our own implementation.

In many cases our own implementation of work with db duplicates
oslo.db code.

Remove:
- manila/common/sqlalchemyutils.py;
- manila/db/sqlalchemy/utils.py;
- manila/db/sqlalchemy/session.py;
- manila/db/sqlalchemy/migration.py;
- DBError, wrap_db_error, InvalidUnicodeParameter exceptions;
- db_sync, db_version, db_version_control, _find_migrate_repo
function

and replace it with appropriate oslo.db functions.

Add 'joinedload' statement to db queries if necessary.

Fix unit tests, clean up test_migrations.py

Implements bp oslo.db

Change-Id: I48a4da797594cf020f67f78024bd0f86b5abd5ef

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-04-24 02:43:57.000000000', 'message': "Fix-sec grp default rules API using Neutron driver

This patch adds the fix for 'os-security-group-default-rules' API
using the Neutron driver which does not have such feature.

If 'conf->security_group_api' is 'neutron' then,
'NativeNeutronSecurityGroupAPI' is being used as security group api
in this API and this neutron API driver (https://github.com/openstack/
nova/blob/master/nova/network/security_group/neutron_driver.py#L48)
does not have any of the function which are being called from this
API class.

This is detected while adding tempest test for this API.
(https://review.openstack.org/#/c/87924/2)

In Neutron, there is no such feature So this Nova API should use the
Nova compute API for their processing instead of neutron deriver.

Change-Id: I4b12b312c13a6f051055de847d9ea515abd62bc4
Closes-Bug: 1311500
"}, {'created': '2014-05-07 06:05:09.000000000', 'message': "Raise NotImplemented from sec grp default rule API

Currently Neutron does not have any interface for
'os-security-group-default-rules'. So raising the NotImplemented error
when this Nova API is being run with Neutron.

If 'conf->security_group_api' is 'neutron' then,
'NativeNeutronSecurityGroupAPI' is being used as security group api
in this API and this neutron API driver does not have any of the
function which are being called from this API class. And throws the
Attribute error.

Defining all the necessary functions in neutron API driver and raising
NotImplemented error from them. Once Neutron is ready with this
functionality then, we will define those function accordingly.

Related-Bug: 1311500

Change-Id: I4b12b312c13a6f051055de847d9ea515abd62bc4

commit_message:
Raise NotImplemented from sec grp default rule API

Currently Neutron does not have any interface for
'os-security-group-default-rules'. So raising the NotImplemented error
when this Nova API is being run with Neutron.
If 'conf->security_group_api' is 'neutron' then,
'NativeNeutronSecurityGroupAPI' is being used as security group api
in this API and this neutron API driver does not have any of the
function which are being called from this API class. And throws the
Attribute error.
Defining all the necessary functions in neutron API driver and raising
NotImplemented error from them. Once Neutron is ready with this
functionality then, we will define those function accordingly.

Related-Bug: 1311500

Change-Id: I4b12b312c13a6f051055de847d9ea515abd62bc4

commit_message:
Move token persistence classes to token.persistence module

Create and move all token persistence code to a new token.persistence
module. This allows the token_provider_api to utilize the token
persistence service without introducing circular dependencies. A proxy
class, that will log a deprecation message if instantiated, has been
created for both the token.core.Manager object and token.core.Driver
object. These proxy objects are slated for removal in the K cycle.

Change-Id: Iae1240c6de4382332b967926efe31f5355554f6e
bp: non-persistent-tokens

commit_message:
Remove SAML unscoped token auth from setup.cfg

This option is only needed for loading from config and from cli
which we don't implement anywhere yet.

Change-Id: I557d7a7e223288d7d4428f89b13820ae2b08855d

commit_message:
Add missing parameters for server rebuild

Currently, nova rebuild only support reset: password, image,
preserve-ephemeral. While nova api support other parameters
like: name, metadata, personality. This patch adds these missing
parameters for server rebuild.

Change-Id: I4edd8146bbbb0b2e0c9e01907af5dab96f090029
Closes-bug: 1268435

commit_message:
Remove duplicate conditional statement

It contains two same conditional statements to check whether the first
argurment is end with '.ring.gz'. The latter one can be covered by 'else'
clause.

Change-Id: I4b67dc330e82e793020bec4b74047062313ae11c
Signed-off-by: Lin Yang <lin.a.yang@intel.com>

To ensure that people do not add messages with _() translations

commit_message:
Add hacking check for explicit import of _

Unit tests are not guaranteed to discover whether
the _() function has been explicitly imported to a file.

To ensure that people do not add messages with _() translations
without importing the function, I am adding this hacking check
to enforce the import of _ when it is needed.

The commit includes fixes for offenders found by the new
check.

Change-Id: I616dce6a9da461b3ad2cfaf5e114a2aaa8ced9fa
Closes-Bug: #1348129

commit_message:
Add log translation hints for Heat

Current oslo libraries support translating log messages using different
translation domains and oslo would like to see hints in all of our code
by the end of juno. So Heat should handle the changes out over the
release.

blueprint log-translation-hints

Change-Id: If0fba45f970ef0618b0bf3fdc46eaa2dc7fac0d0

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly
    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. The more you
    participate in the community the more rewarding it is for you. You may also
    notice that the more you get to know people and get to be known, the faster
    your patches will be reviewed and eventually approved. Get to know others
    and become known by doing code reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a
    great way to learn the code base.

    Thanks again for supporting OpenStack, we look forward to working with you.

commit_message:
Updated _boot_server() to handle floating ip/external networks

The previous code would make use of the external network causing
the test to fail

Closes-Bug: #1347653

Change-Id: I234ae077b6fa9adf5fc64f7c189090d80f904110

commit_message:
Enable hacking checks H305 and H307 in tox.ini template

With the change If1dd9c89f65ede6959865a885777cb08c263eca0 we
enabled the hacking checks H305 and H307. But we forgot to enable
them in the tox.ini template as well.

Change-Id: I67482951aa09ee73546715181701066b1d26343a

commit_message:
Added swift as a trove prerequisite

If you want to use trove for database backups,
you need swift.

The install guide does not state this requirement,
which needs to go on the following page:

http://docs.openstack.org/trunk/install-guide/install/apt/content/trove-install.html

The need to add swift is documented in the
following trove doc scrub etherpad:

https://etherpad.openstack.org/p/trove-doc-items

I added the swift info.

Change-Id: I49102b6c961464f14484797f06949540fe400920
Closes-Bug: #1346438

Oh generators, you are so much fun.

If the file starts with <html then we believe it's a real html
file, and don't add footers / headers and don't escape.

Unit tests are updated because the new generator stacking seemed
to adjust a counter.

Change-Id: I822591450471066fb3cc02cc006ab1dfb79df786
"}]
commit_message:
don't double escape html

Oh generators, you are so much fun.

If the file starts with <html then we believe it's a real html
file, and don't add footers / headers and don't escape.

Unit tests are updated because the new generator stacking seemed
to adjust a counter.

Change-Id: I822591450471066fb3cc02cc006ab1dfb79df786

commit_message:
Clean up openstack-common.conf

Keystonemiddleware doesn't use the config fixture, and it doesn't use
strutils directly, so remove these modules from openstack-common.conf
and re-sync.

Change-Id: I23bc410a6efc2b124bc7bd780b822f05d4204026

commit_message:
Retry when connection to cinder is refused

Currently, cinder client does not retry when connections to cinder
service is refused. There are many legitimate scenarios under which
retry should be attempted:
1) cinder service being restarted;
2) cinder service is running on multiple API nodes behind a LB, which
might be temporarily overwhelmed or being maintained.

In any scenario, retry with a backoff timer does not seem to hurt.

Change-Id: I3c290c59fa67262c4a3473815b4380ee39e24332
Closes-Bug: 1347843

commit_message:
Migrate test_dashboard_basic_ops to tempest clients

Just switched from OfficialClientTest to ScenarioTest because
TestDashboardBasicOps does not use methods of OfficialClientTest.

Change-Id: I3b8eb90e058cde03cb40f120bb2c268f31ae078c

commit_message:
Make manage/unmanage admin only

Manage/Unmanage functionality should be admin
only commands. Make this the default in the policy file.

Change-Id: Ieb71891cdedd36f862f3eaae50174e294417b122

commit_message:
Document Fuel running on vSphere feature

planning-guide -- added 7300-fuel-on-vsphere-prepare to describe how to
configure vSphere to accomodate the Fuel installation.

user-guide -- added fuel-on-vsphere with instructions for installing Fuel
on vSphere.

ref-arch -- add graphic that shows the network topology used

Change-Id: If1faf3d868d1e4256a2b3eb8a4a8cbd7b9675c09

commit_message:
Use compare_digest or an equivalent when available

This avoids the same issue that caused a prior exploit
in nova, we might as well avoid this by doing it correctly
in the first place.

See: https://bugs.launchpad.net/bugs/cve/2014-3517

Change-Id: Iea4b3bcded268de926f32f956383d03fd9f15d59

commit_message:
Explicitly name subscription queue for responses

This prevents response queues being abandoned but still bound to
the exchange with the same key as the newer queue.

Change-Id: Iee0465010a1c6d00e96fb672505688a0f763f86c
Closes-Bug: 1318742
(cherry picked from commit 25f3d9acc395baef730203dcfc3941dbfc4fb73b)

commit_message:
IPMINative to use the new ManagementInterface

Set the new ManagementInterface to the IPMINative driver. As the only
vendor method of the IPMINative driver was the set_boot_device, the
vendor interface is not needed anymore and was removed.

Also, before the 'persistent' parameter of the _set_boot_device() method
was ignored, this patch is fixing it.

Implements: blueprint new-management-interface
Change-Id: I4f3d13f1e0bebda011b3bfbb71ecd7507ca44c39

  https://review.openstack.org/108974

Also, I do not think we should use try_import, and we should do the real import inside the class' __init__ methods because Nova wants this to fail-fast with an ImportError if and only if nova-compute is configured to use the Ironic driver AND the python-ironicclient module is not present. AUIU, it shouldn't fail when importing nova.virt.ironic.driver

commit_message:
Import fixes from the Nova driver reviews

Import fixes from the Nova driver review, based upon revision 7
of https://review.openstack.org/#/c/103167/

- better use of _L* helpers
- dynamically import python-ironicclient when the driver is initialized,
  so that Nova does not need to add it to requirements.txt
- remove unused CONF options pxe_bootfile_name
  and instance_type_extra_specs

Co-authored-by: Devananda van der Veen <devananda.vdv@gmail.com>

Change-Id: Iee1481632e9927766776c7d35264e8cf4c469c8a

commit_message:
Get initial build to work.

Modified build to work with maven 2

Modified so it will download monasca-common jars
from tarballs.openstack.org if the user is jenkins, otherwise the
user is told to build and install monasca-common

Had to move the source code to the new thresh directory so that a
separate module could do the download before dependencies would
be checked by maven

Had to explicitly set the project name in the control file, not sure
why

Change-Id: Ic4d02478b078aad7c1f0eebda2ea2def8d9edf1a

commit_message:
Explicity request an unscoped token

Allow users with a default_project_id to retrieve an unscoped token.

Co-Authored-By: Adam Young <ayoung@redhat.com>
Blueprint: explicit-unscoped
Change-Id: Id145d9b1586e965e667b61844fa54017ae8a5686

Populate repository with common initial files

Every repo needs a first commit, eh? Most of this

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be

    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be

    notice that the more you get to know people and get to be known, the faster
    your patches will be reviewed and eventually approved. Get to know others

    great way to learn the code base.

[{'created': '2014-07-22 09:56:34.000000000', 'message': 'Add SERVICE_TOKEN to the sample local.conf

I expect the sample local.conf file to contain all the required
variables. However, after copying samples/local.conf, the stack.sh
script still asks for SERVICE_TOKEN.

This commit adds the SERVICE_TOKEN definition to local.conf so that a
new user can just copy samples/local.conf, edit it, and have a running
stack.sh without the mild annoyance of having more variables to set.

Change-Id: Ifb163c7f67c80037d8b10458f2df458a20da4667
'}]
commit_message:
Add SERVICE_TOKEN to the sample local.conf

I expect the sample local.conf file to contain all the required
variables. However, after copying samples/local.conf, the stack.sh
script still asks for SERVICE_TOKEN.

This commit adds the SERVICE_TOKEN definition to local.conf so that a
new user can just copy samples/local.conf, edit it, and have a running
stack.sh without the mild annoyance of having more variables to set.

Change-Id: Ifb163c7f67c80037d8b10458f2df458a20da4667

commit_message:
Ensure routing key is specified in the address for a direct producer

Porting this fix from oslo.messaging.  This fixes the impl_qpid.py
driver to allow it to work with the latest stable upstream QPID broker
(version 0.28).  See the Apache Qpid Jira bug
https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPID-5557

Change-Id: If71f78e50f8a9b3acfd1e9d02c8271f17c4ebee7
Closes-Bug: #1300318
(cherry picked from commit a90f0c6cfc44bc3c3fecec2f3b7281902cd6ec19)

(1 comment)

In addition to the comment, I wonder if this is really just about creds anymore. For example, part of the isolated creds code has to do with each neutron network having its own name. Tempest currently does not work with nova-network and vlans because it assumes the fixed network name is global unless you are running neutron with tenant isolation. The current change I think will not support neutron without isolation. Since it is a use case for this change to run without tenant isolation I think this class needs to also supply the fixed network name, which is not really a credential. This class is now really representing what is unique about a user/tenant.'}, {'account_id': 5196, 'date': '2014-07-23 20:25:50.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 9:

(1 comment)

So it probably wasn't clear from just this commit message, but what we decided in Darmstadt was to do the development on the new cred provider iteratively. For the first step we are adding the abstract class interface and a simple cred provider that is just tenant/user pairs, which means only nova-network support. Once the basic mechanism is shown to work we'll add neutron support as the next step when the demand is there.

The network selection code will work the same as the non-isolated code currently does. For neutron support you'll have to use the single user/tenant non-isolated mechanism for now, (which is why we shouldn't be deleting it until neutron support is ready) because there is no network selection mechanism in the first implementation of the cred provider.

I think adding support for other n-net modes support will be very easy to implement here, once we get the common bits landed. Adding a network name to tie to the tenant should be easy and we should be able to handle both cases easily. Having the configuration in yaml gives us some extra flexibility.

I think the name is fine, mostly from a backwards compatibility standpoint. Also, it's a bit of a stretch, but tenants are part of the credentials being returned and if we're dealing with network configuration it's still in the tenant scope, it's just about making sure the creds returned are valid for use."}, {'account_id': 1192, 'date': '2014-07-23 20:59:56.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9: Code-Review+2 Workflow+1

ok, I was not in Darmstadt :). Just wanted to make sure we were covering the networking issues. I do think it would be good to change some of the names once this is done and no-tenant-isolation becomes less of a corner case. Although we get some value out of the keystone stress that isolation provides, it might be better to get that from a keystone stress test given how the current way we do it lets horrible regressions like https://bugs.launchpad.net/nova/+bug/1347156 slip through. But with this new feature we can do both.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-07-23 23:45:03.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9: Verified-1

commit_message:
Add base class for all credential providers

Defines the base interface of all credential providers. User of this
will be the existing isolated_cread provider and the a new user_list
provider.

Change-Id: If382b549428c15ebb2ed850be9e0405e84226f6c
Partially-implements: bp/test-accounts

Neutron does not implement the feature right now, so using Neutron

commit_message:
Mark floating-IP auto-assignment as disabled also with Neutron

Neutron does not implement the feature right now, so using Neutron
is like using Nove-Network with auto-assignment disabled.

See the Neutron spec at:
https://blueprints.launchpad.net/neutron/+spec/auto-associate-floating-ip

Change-Id: If8bbd8adb69bf03649f6c61a6bc9f560a9913fbc

commit_message:
Bump hacking to 0.9.x series

Ignore H904 because it's a deprecated hacking check.
Ignore H405 because it should be fixed with a separate patch.

Change-Id: I2e3bf41474cead1a860810886791e025139cca3b

commit_message:
Lock around source repositories setup

Problems were seen when building images in parallel with
git clones and fetches interfering with each other.

Stop it.

Co-Authored-By: Michael Kerrin <michael.kerrin@hp.com>
Change-Id: Iaa48f259755d8b22327459a5c6d224a342909aee

commit_message:
Fix nodes left in an incosistent state if no workers

This patch is fixing the problem of leaving the nodes in an inconsistent
state if there's no free conductor workers available to deploy or the
tear down a node, the patch is using the set_spawn_error_hook() method
of TaskManager to run some custom code that will rollback the nodes
to the previous provision_state and target_provision_state in case
NoFreeConductorWorker is raised.

Closes-Bug: #1331494
Change-Id: I5d6e8e2c69cbdf1f9abe169afe617aa79783e57d

commit_message:
Add version command to murano-db-manage

Now we can use "murano-db-manage version" to print current
migration version applied to the database.

Change-Id: I933faaacd98b85cfa0b86bfc8c2c70d2548ac573
Closes-bug: #1342259

commit_message:
Catch oslo.db error instead of sqlalchemy error

The latest oslo.db code wraps all sqlalchemy exceptions and re-raise
them as oslo.db exceptions. But there is a single case in Ironic when
we suppose to get sqlalchemy exception, so this will break unittest,
when the new version of oslo.db will come.

Added check for the new oslo.db exception, left the old check for the
compatibility.

Closes-Bug: #1214341
Change-Id: Iae5599948d29778ac416edf31d3b1b2f7a8a54a9

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-07-15 15:51:21.000000000', 'message': 'Implement API to get driver properties

Implement GET /v1/drivers/<driver>/properties that returns a
dictionary of (driver_info) properties of the specified driver.
Each entry in the dictionary is:
  key: name of the property
  value: description of the property

An invalid driver name results in an HTTP 404.

Eg: 'GET /v1/drivers/pxe_ipminative/properties' returns:
{"pxe_deploy_ramdisk": "UUID ... of the ramdisk... Required.",
 "ipmi_username": "IPMI username. Required.",
 "ipmi_address": "IP of the node's BMC. Required.",
 "ipmi_password": "IPMI password. Required.",
 "pxe_deploy_kernel": "UUID ... of the deployment kernel. Required."
}

If the properties for a driver are not cached, the API service makes
an RPC request to a conductor to get the properties for that driver.
It then caches that information for subsequent requests of that driver.

Change-Id: I9c98f4369c54a7cdf9e20ea87348e61f7af10303
Blueprint: get-required-driver-info
Closes-Bug: #1261915

commit_message:
Implement API to get driver properties

Implement GET /v1/drivers/<driver>/properties that returns a
dictionary of (driver_info) properties of the specified driver.
Each entry in the dictionary is:
  key: name of the property
  value: description of the property

An invalid driver name results in an HTTP 404.

Eg: 'GET /v1/drivers/pxe_ipminative/properties' returns:
{"pxe_deploy_ramdisk": "UUID ... of the ramdisk... Required.",
 "ipmi_username": "IPMI username. Required.",
 "ipmi_address": "IP of the node's BMC. Required.",
 "ipmi_password": "IPMI password. Required.",
 "pxe_deploy_kernel": "UUID ... of the deployment kernel. Required."
}

If the properties for a driver are not cached, the API service makes
an RPC request to a conductor to get the properties for that driver.
It then caches that information for subsequent requests of that driver.

Change-Id: I9c98f4369c54a7cdf9e20ea87348e61f7af10303
Blueprint: get-required-driver-info
Partial-Bug: #1261915

commit_message:
trace the world

as we attempt to figure out what's going on with all these fails
in the gate maybe we should default back to tracing the world. The
lack of some of the parameters makes the requests lines not as
useful as we'd like.

Change-Id: I3a5073b1fedb8aecd579f3584272302fc489d8a0

commit_message:
Backporting nova host manager changes into ironic

Some very trivial pep8 fixes need to go back into the ironic tree
in case of future round-trip revisions.  This patch just backports
then so they won't be forgotten.

commit_message:
Don't log sensitive auth data

Add the ability to turn off logging from the session object and then
handle logging of auth requests within their own sections.  This is a
very simplistic ability to completely disable logging.  Logging more
filtered debugging can be added later.

This new ability is utilized in this patch to prevent logging of
requests that include passwords.  This covers authenticate, password
change, and user update requests that include passwords.

SecurityImpact
Change-Id: I3dabb94ab047e86b8730e73416c1a1c333688489
Closes-Bug: #1004114
Closes-Bug: #1327019

commit_message:
[DO NOT MERGE] Fix exception names and CLI args

Fixes two bugs:
* Renames HTTPNotFound -> NotFound to match openstack.common.exceptions
* Fixes positional argument names (package-id -> id with metavar) and
  adds shell tests to check parsing

Change-Id: I36e8ac6249b976d13c36dcd2e6fa654b41ac1a06
Closes-Bug: #1339208

commit_message:
Generalize exception handling in Nova driver

We need to ensure nodes get unprovisioned and disassociated from instances upon
all failure cases, not only the specific exceptions being caught now.  This
removes the catching of those specific exceptions during instance spawn and
performs required cleanup and re-raising.

Change-Id: I9461139400d7aa0a339550cf89f3d49e3a8cb2c0
